	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f98572950214407>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Crowd Control Problems</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Mar 27th 4:45 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=38139><span id= >Aethyrs</span></a><br><span id=notbold>8 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I am a 40th Necro that is in need of some expert advice.&nbsp;&nbsp;I do know that I am not a an enchanter and will fail terribly compared to an enchanter at crowd control. However, many times I will be the closest thing to a crowd controller as there is.<br><br>I am running into 2 problems that you guys may have a solution for.<br><br>Situation:  The group puller pulls a train of Icebone Skeletons (3) to our group.  Everyone says to assist puller...everyone proceeds to bash 1st creature.  Enchanter or myself...root or mezz..or charm or screaming terror(mezz) the other 2.  Wait till first one dies..and move on to next one..etc..<br><br><br>Problem One:<br><br>Assisting.  If everyone assists, one creature will be targeted...leaves the other two for mezzing...etc.  What I am finding is that I will have to get extremely close to the puller, so when I hit assist, it will target the correct monster.  This will give all three of the GIB's a chance to hit me.  If that happens, my pet will jump in and attack the one who hit me...  so it may or may not be the correct target.  So now we have at least 2 skeles that are engaged in melee..<br><br>Problem 2<br><br>How do u select monsters in a very confined space.  I have an assist key...see problem #1.. I also have a select closest npc key (if i use it may or may not be the correct monster that is either supposed to be attacked or mezzed.  So u move closer, just to realiz that all three of the skeletons are moving as one beast and u try to click on the one that is not being bashed on...god only knows which one u select..now Im too close...see problem #1..or I take a chance and cast screaming terror..he resists..see problem 1...  <br><br>Ack...any advice would be greatly appreciated.<br><br>Thanks!<br>Aethyrs<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>4 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99076687961700>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=99076687961700>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99076687961700>RE: Crowd Control Problems</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99076687961700#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, May 25th 1:01 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm sorry, but I find AE mez sloppy and ineffecive.&nbsp;&nbsp;Up to lvl 52, your AE only lasts 16 seconds.  16 seconds is not enough to get anything else done.  At 49+ you can Dazzle, that lasts 96 seconds.  I single target, always, unless I'm raiding green con mobs.  It takes skill and practice, you have to learn to click in the exact spot to get the right mob, and if you can't do that, walk right up to the fight and color flux 'em.  That usually gets the unmezed ones rooted out.  Good tanks know how to split pulls up, but if they can't you can.  Another dirty little trick...clerics tend to attract unmezed mobs, they have decent ac too, so sometimes, if nothing else, the cleric accidentally splits em for you.<br><br>Tarnin Austa, 52 enchanter</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
