	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok im just going to say what i do and hope this helps some. I am a lvl 52 enchanter and have been mezzing and doing crowd control the same way with no chances since in the 30's. Number one, pet while grouped = death to you and possibly your whole group. If one of the mobs hits you forget the mez because that pet is not going to get off that mob until its dead or the mob is. Number two, if there are more then 2 mobs coming I always AE mez. If your in a small room and you mez yourself (which happens to me often as i hunt in dungeons), then your going to get hit but soon as the mez wears off of you mez again. You may keep mezzing yourself but your keeping the mobs mezzed as well. Number three, if there are 2 mobs I use single target mez for the add. Always keep both single and AE up. If I cant target the add within a few seconds i just AE. Its better to mez both even tho there is only one add then to let the other stay unmezzed and beat the crap out of the tanks. I hope that helps a little. It has worked for me so far.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
